theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_and_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 (A : Set X)) :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- From `hA_closed` and `hP1` we have `closure (interior A) = A`.
  have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = A :=
    closure_interior_eq_of_isClosed_and_P1 (A := A) hA_closed hP1
  -- An equality of the form `closure (interior A) = A` implies that `A` is open.
  exact isOpen_of_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hEq

theorem isClosed_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    IsClosed (closure (interior (A : Set X))) := by
  -- The closure of any set is closed.
  simpa using
    (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (interior (A : Set X))))
